
                                   Vimperator
                                   ==========

Opening web pages
Navigating Web Sites
Working With Document
Working With Marks
Tab Movement
Miscellaneous Commands

Shortcuts
---------
   gh    Hacker News
   gob   BPI Express Online Banking
   gof   Fedora Project
   gog   Gmail Account
   goi   Inquirer Newspaper
   gok   Kernel Newbies
   gol   LinuxToday
   gon   News Google
   gop   Philippine Star Newspaper
   gor   Running Reddit

   NOTE: To display all Quickmarks, press :qmarks

Opening web pages
-----------------

   Open one or more URLs in the current tab:
   Press 'o' - Shortcut for open
      :o linux tutorial - Search Google for "linux tutorial"
      :o /etc/fstab - Open local file
      :o reddit.com, linuxtoday.com, osnews.com - open multiple URLs

   Press 't' - Shortcut for tabopen, similar function to 'open' but uses new
   tab.

   Press 'T' - Show 't' prompt containing the current URL.  Useful if you wish
   to go somewhere by editing the URL of the current page.

   Press 'O' - Similar to 'T' but uses the current window.

   Press 'w' - Similar to 'o' but opens web page in new window.

   Press 'y' - Copy current URL.
   Press 'p' - Paste URL based on the current clipboard content.


Navigating Web Sites
--------------------
   Press 'L' or 'CTRL-o' - Go back one page in browser history.
      :ba - Similar to pressing 'ctrl-o'
      :ba! - Go back to the beginning of the browser history
      :[count]ba - Go back nth pages.

   Press 'H' or 'CTRL-i' - Go forward one page in browser history.
      :fo - Similar to pressing 'CTRL-i'.
      :fo! - Go forward to the latest web page
      :[count]fo - Go forward to nth page.

   :ju - Show the tab's session history.  Useful for :ba and :fo

   Press 'gh' - Opens homepage in current tab.
   Press 'gH' - Opens homepage in new tab.
   Press 'gu' - Go to parent directory.
   Press 'gU' - Go to root directory.

   Press 'r' - Force reloading of the current web page
   Press 'R' - Force reloading but skip cache

   Press 'Ctrl-c' - Stop loading the current page

   :sav [file] - Save current page to disk.  If [file] is omitted, use page's
      default filename.

   :winc - Close all other tab except current window.
   :q - Quit current tab.
   :qa - Quit all open tab and don't save sessions.
   :xa - Save all sessions and quit.

   Press 'f' - Show hints and allows you to follow links on pages by typing it's
         unique integer number.
   Press 'F' - Same as 'f' but open link in new tab.


Working With Document
---------------------

   Press '0' - Scroll to the absolute left of the document.
   Press '$' - Scroll to the absolute right of the document.
   Press 'gg' - Go to top of the page.
   Press 'G' - Go to the end of the page.
   Press '[count]%' - Scroll to percent of the document.
   Press '[count] h j k l' - Cursor movement
   Press 'Ctrl-b' - Scroll up full page.
   Press 'Ctrl-u' - Scroll down full page.
   Press '<Tab>' - Keyboard focus to the next element.
   Press '<S-Tab>' - Rewind keyboard focus.
   Press '[count]gi' - Focus last used input field.
   Press ']]' - Follow the link labeled 'next' or '>'.
   Press '[[' - Follow the link labeled 'back' or '<'.

   Press 'zi' - Enlarge text of current page: zoom in.
   Press 'zo' - Reduce text of current page: zoom out.

   Press 'y' - Yank current URL.
   Press 'Y' - Copy current selected text.
   Press 'p' - Paste text on the clipboard.

Working With Marks
------------------

   Press 'M<a-z,A-Z,0-9>' - Mark URL (bookmarks or quick marks)
   Press 'a' - Add a bookmark, using default title
   Press 'A' - Toggle on/off bookmark
      :bma -t='custom title' -keyword=kw url


Tab Movement
------------

   Press 'B' - Show all opened tab (buffer list).
   Press '[count]b' - Goto specified buffer from the buffer list.
   Press 'g0' - Goto the first tab.
   Press 'g$' - Goto the last tab.
   Press 'Ctrl-n' - Goto the next tab. Cycle to the first tab when at last tab.
   Press 'gt' - Goto the next tab.
   Press 'gT' - Goto the previous tab.
   Press 'd' - Close current tab.

   :tabo - Close all other tab except current one.
   :undoa[ll] - Undo closing of all closed tab (up to 10 closed tab).

   Press '<Ctrl-^>' - Toggle to previously selected tab.

Miscellaneous Commands
----------------------

   Show Firefox toolbar (by default, tool is disabled)
      :set guioptions=mT


   Disable Firefox toolbar manually
      :set guioptions=

   Show all the standard GUI button:
      :set go+=mTB
      :set go=

   Press 'Ctrl-z' - To set pass-through mode (for using Gmail shortcut)
   Press 'Esc' key - To back to normal mode

   Press ':cd [path]' - Change current directory
   Press ':pwd' - Print current directory.
